events.name: TensorFlow Dev Summit Extended + Machine Learning Crash Course!
events.description:
TensorFlow Dev Summit brings together a diverse mix of machine learning users from around the world for a full day of highly technical talks, demos, and conversation with the TensorFlow team and community. In TensorFlow Dev Summit EXTENDED we will watch together the recorded TensorFlow summit.
We will include a Machine Learning Crash Course for those who wish to learn about Machine Learning from a practical, applied perspective that will enable them to use machine learning within their every day projects, and who wish to benefit from the power.

There's more! After the event, you are expected to complete the Machine Learning course material from where we left off at the event. Each participant will be asked to periodically present what they have learned to demonstrate their grasp of the material. Attendance and participation will be marked and Certificates will be awarded at the end of the course.

venue.name: TwoFour54 #thelab (lime coloured building)
venue.address_1: Behind Ministry of Labor Office, Opposite Khalifa Park P.O.Box: 2454

events.description:
Couldn't catch up with Google I/O? Don't worry – we've got you covered.
Join us for Google I/O Extended here in Abu Dhabi, and hear all about the key announcements from Google.

I/O Extended events include a variety of options for developers—from live streaming sessions to local demos, hackathons, codelabs, and more.

Join us for some Google fun and a chance to network with industry professionals!

Agenda:
(5pm - 6pm) : registration
(6:00 - 6:30) : Google IO 2018 Highlights!
(6:30 - 7:00) : networking session + break
(7:00 - 7:30) : workshop 1 ( Google Colab, the Online, Zero-setup, Python Notebook Environment that Kicks Ass! )
-break-
(7:40 - 8:00): workshop 2 (Firebase in IoT)

Workshop details:
Workshop 1:
Title: Google Colab, the Online, Zero-setup, Python Notebook Environment that Kicks Ass!
Duration: 20-30 minutes
Level: Intermediate
Requirements: Laptop, Google account, some Python programming
Brief Description: This talk introduces Google Colab, a Python environment that gets you coding in no time, no installation needed. Save, share and collaborate in real-time with your peers, all within the Google Drive ecosystem. Create reusable, configurable, and presentable documents for your assignments or labs. Get access to GPU powered runtime to do some serious machine learning explorations.

Workshop 2:
Title : Firebase in IoT
Duration: 10-15 minutes
Level: Beginners
Requirements: download Android Studio + Arduino IDE
Brief description: you will learn how to use firebase database in IoT and control IoT. You will be able to connect a ESP8266 to firebase database and send the distance from ultrasonic sensor. Then connect a mobile app to firebase and control an LED using Android mobile app.
